I got pulled over by 6 cop cars all tactical formation had their semi automatics guns pointed at my vehicle. At that moment I felt the world for me has come to end scared coz any slit mistake I do put my hand down would be shot at.  I did all they asked me to do handcuffed put me in the back of their cruiser. Reason they kept saying someone has been reported to have guns in the area so gave them go head to search my vehicle found NOTHING. They got me out their cruiser sat at the curb side told them reason why I was in that area to see my girlfriend. All in that at the moment alot is circling in my mind if nothing is found why can't they let me go, is it the car that I'm driving or what is an African American doing in this particular area. Here is what I don't understand at the curb side I was told stand face one of their vehicles with flash light "on their radio didn't match description who they were looking for coz they used a code." They put back in vehicle again to search in the data base if I had any pending arrest warrants. <rate>5<//rate>< Review>
I am currently 5 months pregnant and was extremely worried about a dentist still pushing X-rays so was very careful in where I chose to go. After reading many, many reviews and asking for recommendations on the local Facebook group, Hada Family Dental was recommended and I decided to schedule. In addition to me being pregnant, I am also diagnosed with Hyperemesis gravidarum. HG is a pregnancy complication that is characterized by severe nausea, vomiting, weight loss, and possibly dehydration. Feeling faint may also occur so I was very worried about a simple teeth cleaning as I cannot even hold water down at this moment. Upon checking in, I threw up 3 times in the bathroom and was worried I might have to reschedule. The staff advised me that ironically, 5 of the staff are pregnant including my dental hygienist, Cori Salazar, RDH. It made me feel more comfortable regarding my care so I moved forward with the appointment and it was truly the best experience I could've had given my situation. I think I was a hard patient as my nausea was constant and I had to keep getting up to take a minute so I don't throw up, but Cori was absolutely nothing less than exemplary. She was so professional, so courteous and so understanding that I was in utter disbelief. She took her time cleaning my teeth and let me take as many breaks as possible, even if that meant keeping me after they close. She even offered to split the cleaning appointment into two if it was too much for me to handle at once. I have never received such amazing service as this in my life. Not to mention, I was provided with a business card to call at any time I needed to, even after hours, in case I had any concerns at all. Now that is service that I will keep coming back for. My husband and son will be coming in for an appointment soon and I am very confident that we will be lifetime clients of Hada Family Dental. Superb experience!</Review>

<rate>5</rate>< Review>
I was referred to Hada Family Dental from a dear friend of mine a little over a month ago. Friend referrals are the best -- super honest and extremely trustworthy. I am very particular with my overall dental health care and had yet to find a practice in OC that I genuinely liked. Personally, a dental hygienist makes or breaks my experience (they do all of the important work!) My friend couldn't stop raving about her dental hygienist, KELLEY!!! I knew I was overdue for a cleaning, so I booked an appointment with her immediately. When I scheduled my appointment I learned that Kelley's first available was a little over a month out. I was completely fine with that, in fact, I took it as a great sign. I want someone who is popular and busy.

This morning was my first appointment...The office is absolutely beautiful, immaculate, and state of the art. The front office personnel was warm and welcoming upon arrival (despite my tardiness). I had my new patient paper work and insurance information filled out in advance. The new patient forms are easily accessible on their website. So convenient!

My actual teeth cleaning with Kelley was a breeze. During my cleaning I watched television on a flat screen mounted to the ceiling (amazing) and kicked back in the comfortable oversized chair. Not only did Kelley make me feel extremely comfortable, but she thoroughly explained every single move she was making. She gave suggestions to improve gum health without lecturing and provided suggestions for preventative care. Kelley is a real gem and I could not be more grateful for the referral.
Her cleaning was meticulous and my teeth feel great. I HIGHLY recommend Kelley!! She's well worth the wait!</Review>

< text>
If you want to go to a dental practice that takes care of you from the moment you walk through the door this is your place. All the staff (front office, RDA's, RDH's) are all so friendly and have ample experience so you know you're in good hands. Of course the owner, Dr. Hada, who is a family friend, is an exceptional Dentist!

Today for example I got an old silver filling taken out and it was replaced with white composite. Eber, the RDA, was very nice and numbed my gums prior to the maxillary nerve block shot. When Dr. Hada went in with the shot I didn't feel a thing! This is mostly due to the fact that he took his time to slowly release the numbing agent. I appreciated him putting my comfort level as a priority, most dentists probably wouldn't have taken the time to do that since they have many patients to see. He also walked me through what he was doing and made sure I was comfortable during the whole procedure. Its little things like that that make a huge difference in a dental visit. I am already looking forward to my next cleaning.

Call and make an appointment today, you will not regret it!<//text>

This review is long overdue!  We have been going to Dr. Hada for many years, first at OC Dental Specialists then when we followed him to Hada Family Dental.

<name>Elwood J. Hullinger</name>< review>
Huge fan of Dr. Hada and his staff. He replaced some silver fillings of mine that were long overdue for replacement. What I especially appreciated was that there was one tooth that possibly needed a root canal, but he wasn't eagerly looking to do the more costly procedure (I automatically think that everyone is like a bad auto mechanic and will do everything to upsell and make a buck) and given that the tooth looked healthy, we did the "wait and see" approach, and the pain subsided eventually -- as he had predicted. That kind of honesty and expertise goes a long way with me. He's also been great with my 6 and 4 year olds, so it's nice to have a 1 stop shop.

UPDATE: I've been a patient of Dr. Hada's for a long time and I try to see him still even though I now live in Salt Lake City. This week I was in town for work and tried to get in to see Dr. Hada but he wasn't able to accommodate on such short notice, but luckily Dr. Chase Carlston was able to see me and I was able to get the work done during my short trip to California. Thanks Dr. Carlston, and good job Hada Family Dental for bringing in another solid dds.< /review>

<userid>115893200904160586609</userid><username>Carter Hiyama</username><gmap_id>0x80e913845aa97c5d:0x21983089bf0dca97< /gmap_id>< Review>
After a friend recommended EZ Automotive to me, I called and spoke with John about coolant in my oil. He quickly texted me with a quote much lower than anywhere else and believe me, I did my research. I called just about every auto repair shop in Santa Barbara. John's quote was the lowest and he was also a pleasure to work with.

We thoroughly weighed my options and he contacted me just about every day on the progress on my new engine. Not once did I feel like he was trying to squeeze money out of me or pressure me into a more expensive repair like some other shops do.

At the end, I mentioned to John that the inside of my car was dirty from sitting there with the windows down on a windy day at the shop and he had the interior wiped up and had the exterior washed for free. Also, he waived the extra labor involved due to some unforeseen problems with a part that I had supplied to him for the job.

John and his only other mechanic, Sebastian, are great guys and perform honest work. I'll be bringing my car only here for future work.

To sum it up: Low prices and unbeatable service. There isn't much more you can ask for. Their 5 star rating you see on here and Yelp isn't a fluke either. They really are the best shop in town.</Review>

<Review>I went to Freeway after being frustrated by the whole online quote experience. I literally was bombarded by text and telephone by lead representatives who were relentless. It was a huge turn off.

After searching for a local agency I found Freeway. The hours were great, location nearby and the website was super informative and full of resources a person might need. I was sold. I went down to the office at 6 pm and was greeted and asked to sign in. Within a few minutes a young man named Christian approached me to let me know he would be assisting me. After I completed a few fields on a form we sat at a COVID safe counter and discussed my car insurance needs. He listened carefully and I gave him my id  and car registration. After about 5 minutes, he returned with an amazing quote, full coverage, good deductible and a premium I could afford. Not only was he professional and efficient, he also caught on that money was tight. I was there for less than 45 minutes. When I left I couldn‚Äôt believe how easy the process was and how quickly I was in and out, but also how great the service was. Now I have the piece of mind of a good policy and a go to person at Freeway. My friend who was with me was so impressed that she is considering changing her insurance to Freeway (and she has several cars). Thank you Christian Martinez for a job well done!</Review><pictures>None< /pictures>< Resp>

< Text>
FANTASTIC dental office!! I cannot sing enough praises about this place. The staff is incredibly friendly, and the dentists are thorough and informative.

I'm not a big fan of dentists, but I felt completely at ease and comfortable the whole time. I had to get a filling fixed and wasn't looking forward to the shots that numb. I didn't even feel them! No slight pinch, NOTHING!!!

I HIGHLY recommend this office, you will not be disappointed.< /Text>

I rarely write bad reviews but in this particular case I do feel like it is important for people NOT to visit this dental practice as they did me a huge disservice and tarnished my trust in dentists.  This was my first dental visit in 8 months in a new city.  They refused to do a routine cleaning due to the fact that they believed I needed a deep cleaning but diagnosed me with no cavities.  I found it hard to believe that as a routine dentist go-er (religiously every 6 months) that all of my numbers were so bad that a routine cleaning would be dangerous/ineffective.  I'm proactive about my dental health and generally know my gum numbers.  I (3 months later) went to another dentist that came highly recommended by a friend- they did the routine cleaning and diagnosed me with 5 cavities.  I ended up getting 2 crowns and filled the other 3.  I moved and ended up with a 3rd opinion- who also said that a deep cleaning was not necessary and that indeed from the XRay's they would have diagnosed the same cavities.  I'm not sure what this office's motivation was for refusing to do a general cleaning- if it was money, they sure missed out because I ended up getting $2k+ worth of dental work done else where.  I was especially upset as I took time away from my newborn to get this done.  Awful experience and I hope no one experiences the same.  I was seen by Haider Farris.</text>

<Review>Quick words to describe Mira Mesa Dental: Accommodating, Caring, Friendly. Let's start with the office, modern amenities. I mean cmon now they have a complimentary massage chair! They've got a keurig, they have magazines galore, your friends are going to want to take you to the dentist just so they can hang out in the lobby. While the dentists are drillin' the waiting room is Netflix and chillin' on the big screen. Located on the second floor so you can check yourself out in the elevator mirrors or if you're in then new year new me hype you can take the stairs for a quick workout. Next, the front desk, they always check insurance and verify your coverage. They send reminders. (They actually call you back when you leave a message, believe it!) Text message reminder? Check. Don't have a cell phone cause big brother is watching? They'll send you a postcard! I routinely get my cleanings from Dr. Martinez. She is passionate about her profession and it reflects in her care for your dental health. I recently had to get my crown replaced by Dr. Faris. < Review>
I have purchased the Blue Spring Kit & the Coolant Bypass System for my Ford. Ordering was easy. The coolant system arrived as promised, easy to understand directions. The Blue Spring became back ordered 10 days. I received an email informing me of the delay.

When I called customer service, Sean was very apologetic. He offered to help locate a shop that had it, if I needed before their delivery date.

The equipment was high quality machined & everything fit perfectly! The Blue Kit delivers the added fuel psi & the throttle response is great! The coolant system is also high quality parts & gives me the confidence that the Wix filter is keeping my engine free of contaminates.

I have friends who have purchased other items with great outcomes as well! Superb quality parts & great customer service equals a happy customer!<//Review>

<user_id>107242694868200467326< /user_id>< username>
matthew rountree</username>
<Time>1554697682540</Time><Rating>4</Rating>< text>
They said it couldn't be done

Actually putting the Sinister oil bypass kit on a ram 6.7 with dual radiators it's pretty simple. All it took was putting a shim under the third bolt position and tipping the filter down far enough so that it didn't distort the hoses going to the radiator it works fine but it would be a lot better if they add two or three inches to the discharge line because I could have tipped it more and still had room to get the canister on from the bottom except I was starting to stretch the discharge line like a guitar string so I had to tip it back up thus somewhat distorting the radiator hoses.

I didn't really care what it was going to take to put the kit in ... it was going to go in because I don't really want to run soot though my bearings and as it turned out it was very simple to do .

So hopefully they'll figure out that all they have to do is lower the point of contact with the hoses and extend the discharge line to make it just as easy to put on a dual radiator system as a standard radiator system<//text>

<user_name>Ted Gifford< /user_name><Text>Do not use the web chat/email service.  They will not respond to that.  You will need to call, wait up to 10 minutes for a live helpful response to your questions.  If you need mike from the fab shop, wait another 10 minutes after the initial wait.  Have your cell phone fully charged.

All but one of my orders had fast delivery and quality parts.  Either made by sinister diesel or by others.

My only concern is of the weld integrity of their headers.  However, I was reassured after sending pictures and another phone call, that there have been no header cracking or other failures.  That these were full penetration welds and that they have a life time warranty.  We may find out more with this product.  I do not have that comfy feeling on the header quality.  The lack of fillet welds worries me.

Otherwise, no issues yet.  Thanks for the help guys<//Text>< Date>

<Resp>None</Resp><Date>1493738452749<//Date>< review>
I have ordered from Sinister twice. Both times, no problems. Both were web orders, and both shipped quickly (items delivered inside of a week, but I am in CA.). I've never dealt with anyone in person, or on the phone. Maybe they are jerks in person, but I would never know. They've had what I needed, so I'll continue to be a customer until there's a reason not to be.
Being in the retail business myself, I see a lot of these 1 star reviews among a sea 5 star reviews and there is always more to the story than the complainer let's on. Usually the customer is just a pain in the a$$ and will never be happy. Many times the customer is just flat out wrong, but the internet has given every whiner a voice, so there you go. Frequently it is actually the distributor or manufacturer that is the reason parts are delayed. No company is perfect, and sometimes problems occur. That doesn't mean a company is bad or dishonest. You'll just have to give them a shot and find out for yourself. I'm happy with them, if that makes any difference.</review>

< Rate>
5<//Rate>
< Review>
I had a major melt down with my12 year old 2005 6.0 Power Stroke Diesel Excursion. Oil Cooler ruptured internally and pumped 4 quarts of oil into my radiator. I went to the Web site for Sinister Diesel and did some initial research and then contacted Eric by Phone. He was most helpful and I ordered a package deal. It had an updated Oil Cooler, new design EGR Cooler, upgraded Stand Pipes, Dummy Plugs, HPOP update kit, upgraded Turbo Oil Feed Line, Drain Tube, Blue Spring kit, Bypass Oil filter kit, Bypass Coolant filter kit and all the necessary filters, gaskets and hardware to get the job done right the first time. I had looked elsewhere for most of this stuff, but the packaging and completeness of there kits are second to none and the price was right. I feel my 6.0 PSD should last me a long time now.< /Review>
